    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Quotes the Joint Board’s recommendation (see ante, telegram from the Acting
                    Secretary of the Navy, December 13) and proceeds:]</p>
                <p>Your Legation has been frequently assured by the Government of Panama—of its own
                    volition and without mention of any treaty provision that might be relevant—that
                    it would not conclude any negotiation for any form of telegraphic communication
                    on the Isthmus without securing the assent of this Government. You will discuss
                    this matter with the Minister for Foreign Affairs and report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
